h3. Summary
Pagination is not working for pipelines endpoint in API 2

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# A repo with more than 10 Pipelines builds is needed to reproduce
# Execute the following curl command:

{code}
#!curl

curl --request GET --user username:password https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/<username>/<repo-slug>/pipelines/
{code}

h3. Expected Results
The output returns a paginated collection with a "next" field, including the link to the next page

h3. Actual Results
The "next" field is missing from the output.

h3. Workaround
Add a query parameter of the page, e.g. if you want to access the 2nd page:

{code}
#!curl

curl --request GET --user username:password https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/<username>/<repo-slug>/pipelines/?page=2
{code}

The reference git-shell implementation provides "~/git-shell-commands" feature - executable files in the directory are available from within restricted shell. That can be used to provide various additional features, e.g. listing repositories, creating or destroying, accesible via shell.

The idea is to provide basic repository management via shell:

{code}
#!python
ssh git@bitbucket.org list|ls [<namespace>]- list own repositories, list repositories from within namespace that current user has access to
ssh git@bitbucket.org create [--public] <repository> - create private, public repository
ssh git@bitbucket.org destroy [--force] <repository> - destroy repository, by default ask user to type repository name, --force allows to skip check i.e. for non-interactive removal
{code}

